## PHASE 0: SETUP & ORIENTATION
> Run once at the start of the workshop.

### Step 0.1 — Identify your company
```
Tool: mcp_neonpanel_account_list_companies
Goal: Get your company_id for all subsequent calls.
```

### Step 0.2 — Map your product family
```
Tool: mcp_neonpanel_account_lookup_asin_catalog
Parameters: company_id, search by Parent ASIN or product name
Goal: Get the Parent ASIN and all Child ASINs (variations).
       Save these — every call below uses them.
```

### Step 0.3 — Check RYG thresholds
```
Tool: mcp_neonpanel_brand_analytics_list_ryg_thresholds
Parameters: company_id
Goal: See current Red/Yellow/Green threshold definitions.
       Optionally customize with write_ryg_thresholds.
```

---

## PHASE 1: MARKET & DISCOVERY DATA (Chapter 4, 5, 6)
> The "Growth" input. Understand where the market is and where you stand.

### Step 1.1 — Search Query Performance (SQP)
```
Tool: mcp_neonpanel_brand_analytics_analyze_search_query_performance
Parameters: company_id, asin(s), reporting_range
Goal: Get all keywords + Purchase Share + RYG classification.
       This is the primary input for Keyword Gap Analysis (Ch. 4).
Output: List of keywords with search volume, impression/click/cart/purchase share.
```

### Step 1.2 — Search Catalog Performance (SCP)
```
Tool: mcp_neonpanel_brand_analytics_analyze_search_catalog_performance
Parameters: company_id, asin(s), reporting_range
Goal: Full funnel view (Impressions → Clicks → Carts → Purchases).
       Diagnose WHERE the funnel breaks (Ch. 2).
Output: Funnel metrics per ASIN, conversion rates at each stage.
```

### Step 1.3 — Keyword Funnel Deep-Dive
```
Tool: mcp_neonpanel_brand_analytics_get_keyword_funnel_metrics
Parameters: company_id, asin(s), specific keywords from Step 1.1
Goal: Per-keyword funnel breakdown for gap keywords.
       See exactly where you lose on each target keyword (Ch. 4).
```

### Step 1.4 — Search Term Momentum
```
Tool: mcp_neonpanel_brand_analytics_get_search_term_momentum
Parameters: company_id, asin(s)
Goal: Identify accelerating vs. declining keywords.
       Prioritize growing keywords, deprioritize declining ones (Ch. 4, 6).
Output: Momentum signals (accelerating / stable / declining) per keyword.
```

### Step 1.5 — Competitive Landscape
```
Tool: mcp_neonpanel_brand_analytics_get_competitive_landscape
Parameters: company_id, asin(s)
Goal: See Top 3 products on each keyword + weak leader detection.
       Determine contestability of gap keywords (Ch. 4, 5).
Output: Leader purchase share, competitive density, weak-leader flags.
```

### Step 1.6 — Conversion Leak Analysis
```
Tool: mcp_neonpanel_brand_analytics_get_conversion_leak_analysis
Parameters: company_id, asin(s)
Goal: Diagnose funnel leaks (impression→click, click→cart, cart→purchase).
       Feeds listing optimization priorities (Ch. 2, 4).
```

---

## PHASE 2: ADVERTISING DATA (Chapter 5, 6)
> The "Enrichment" input. Understand what you're paying for and its incremental value.

### Step 2.1 — PPC Search Terms
```
Tool: mcp_neonpanel_advertising_analyze_search_terms
Parameters: company_id, profile_id, date range, optional asin filter
Goal: Get all PPC search terms with spend, clicks, sales, CPC.
       Cross-reference with SQP for Incrementality Check (Ch. 5).
       Find Blue Oceans by comparing vs. SQP keywords (Ch. 6).
Output: Search term performance including attributed sales, CPC, conversion rate.
```

### Step 2.2 — Campaign Performance
```
Tool: mcp_neonpanel_advertising_analyze_campaign_performance
Parameters: company_id, profile_id, date range
Goal: Campaign-level metrics: spend, sales, ACoS, TACoS.
       Calculate overall advertising efficiency (Ch. 5).
Output: Campaign breakdown with TACoS, ROAS, spend trends.
```

### Step 2.3 — Cross-Sell Opportunities
```
Tool: mcp_neonpanel_brand_analytics_get_cross_sell_opportunities
Parameters: company_id, asin(s)
Goal: Find keywords where buyers of related products also purchase yours.
       Discover untapped keyword channels (Ch. 6).
```

---

## PHASE 3: OPERATIONS & PROFITABILITY (Chapter 7, 8)
> The "Engine" input. Know your true costs and inventory constraints.

### Step 3.1 — Landed Cost
```
Tool: mcp_neonpanel_cogs_get_inventory_landed_cost
Parameters: company_id, sku(s) or asin(s)
Goal: Get per-unit landed cost (manufacturing + freight + duties).
       Calculate True Contribution Margin (Ch. 7).
Output: Landed cost breakdown per SKU.
```

### Step 3.2 — FIFO COGS Analysis
```
Tool: mcp_neonpanel_cogs_analyze_fifo_cogs
Parameters: company_id, date range
Goal: Understand how COGS changes as different batches sell through.
       More accurate margin tracking (Ch. 7).
```

### Step 3.3 — Profit & Loss
```
Tool: mcp_neonpanel_financials_analyze_profit_and_loss
Parameters: company_id, date range
Goal: Full P&L view: revenue, FBA fees, commissions, ad spend, COGS, net margin.
       Validate True Contribution Margin at product level (Ch. 7).
```

### Step 3.4 — Stock Replenishment Risk
```
Tool: mcp_neonpanel_supply_chain_list_stock_replenishment_risk_items
Parameters: company_id
Goal: Identify SKUs at risk of stockout.
       Determine Marketing Throttle mode per SKU (Ch. 8).
Output: Days of supply, risk level, restock urgency per item.
```

### Step 3.5 — FBA Replenishment Candidates
```
Tool: mcp_neonpanel_supply_chain_list_fba_replenishment_candidates
Parameters: company_id
Goal: See what needs to be shipped to FBA now (Ch. 8).
```

### Step 3.6 — Sales Velocity
```
Tool: mcp_neonpanel_supply_chain_analyze_sales_velocity
Parameters: company_id, asin(s)
Goal: Current unit velocity and burn rate.
       Validate the Days of Supply calculation (Ch. 8).
```

### Step 3.7 — Logistics Lead Times
```
Tool: mcp_neonpanel_supply_chain_list_product_logistics_parameters
Parameters: company_id
Goal: Lead time per product (manufacturing + transit + receiving).
       Calculate Last Possible Launch Date (Ch. 8).
```

### Step 3.8 — PO Placement Candidates
```
Tool: mcp_neonpanel_supply_chain_list_po_placement_candidates
Parameters: company_id
Goal: Recommended purchase orders to place now (Ch. 8).
```

### Step 3.9 — Inbound Shipment Tracking
```
Tool: mcp_neonpanel_supply_chain_shipment_arrival_oracle
Parameters: company_id
Goal: Track inbound shipments — when will stock arrive? (Ch. 8)
```

---

## PHASE 4: SYNTHESIS & GOVERNANCE BASELINE (Chapter 9, 10)
> Combine all data into the Growth Machine dossier.

### Step 4.1 — Generate Sales Forecast
```
Tool: mcp_neonpanel_forecasting_generate_sales_forecast
Parameters: company_id, asin(s), horizon
Goal: Forward-looking demand forecast to validate inventory planning.
```

### Step 4.2 — Repeat Purchase Analysis
```
Tool: mcp_neonpanel_brand_analytics_analyze_repeat_purchases
Parameters: company_id, asin(s)
Goal: Understand repeat purchase rates and customer retention.
       Input for lifetime value calculations.
```

### Step 4.3 — Historical Reports (for Week-over-Week baseline)
```
Tool: mcp_neonpanel_account_list_reports
Parameters: company_id
Goal: List available historical reports.

Tool: mcp_neonpanel_account_get_report_details
Parameters: report_id
Goal: Pull specific report data for WoW comparison.
```

